      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW AMALFI (1) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at Bendigo in a handy 28.61 beating Kunama Namadgi. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Well placed and will be tough to beat. GREYSYND BONNIE (4) turned spotting a big start finishing fifth (35.47) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Better than last start and can bounce back. NEENA BALE (5) has missed the frame at her last two but did run well three back when second (30.82) in a Grade 5 at this track. Has the ability and expected to do much better. BUN QUAKE (2) should be thereabouts.",
